description.narrative: By 2025, Ministries of Health and implementing partners have strengthened capacity to deliver quality immunization services., which contributes to Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, more neonates, infants and children survive and thrive, and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth.

title.narrative: By 2025, Ministries of Health and implementing partners have strengthened capacity to deliver quality immunization services.

description.narrative: UNICEF and its implementing partners, in collaboration with the respective Ministries of Health, ensured the continuity of immunization services in the context of COVID-19 pandemic. The proportion of children under 1 who received 3 doses of DPT-containing antigen rose from 71 percent in 2020 to 90.2;percent in 2021, surpassing the annual 76 percent target.Meanwhile, 4.7;percent of the adult population were partially vaccinated (743,363;adults) and 5.4;percent(846,167;adults) were fully vaccinated against COVID-19. The national target (20%) is expected to be achieved in 2022, with a large volume of vaccines in pipeline. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/12/2021
